```
git clone -b script-crash git@github.com:slapin/generate-city-urho3d.git
```

or using web interface:

https://github.com/slapin/generate-city-urho3d/tree/script-crash

Not all data sets lead to this problem. Neither data used here use Urho objects,
only primitive types. I guess depends on array sizes but I don't really know,
arrays never grow more than 1000 items. First few iteration of process_queue always succeed,
then problem starts. The processing happens on new instance of object every time.

